<h1>
java - What references the <id> value of a Maven plugin execution? - Stack Overflow
<\h1>
<p>In a Maven <code>&lt;plugin&gt;</code> element there is an <code>&lt;executions&gt;</code> element which contains multiple <code>&lt;execution&gt;</code> elements. Each <code>&lt;execution&gt;</code> element can have an <code>&lt;id&gt;</code> element containing a string. What references those <code>&lt;id&gt;...&lt;/id&gt;</code> elements? What does it mean to omit that element? What are the semantics of the <code>&lt;id&gt;</code> element?</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;project&gt;
  [...]
  &lt;build&gt;
    &lt;plugins&gt;
      &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;executions&gt;
          &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;default-jar-execution&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
              &lt;finalName&gt;mainjar&lt;/finalName&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
          &lt;/execution&gt;
          &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;extra-jar-execution&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;goals&gt;
              &lt;goal&gt;jar&lt;/goal&gt;
            &lt;/goals&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
              &lt;finalName&gt;anotherjar&lt;/finalName&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
          &lt;/execution&gt;
        &lt;/exectutions&gt;
      &lt;/plugin&gt;
      [...]
    &lt;/plugins&gt;
  &lt;/build&gt;
&lt;/project&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>What references those <code>&lt;id&gt;default-jar-execution&lt;/id&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;id&gt;extra-jar-execution&lt;/id&gt;</code> values? What is the behavioral difference of changing either of those strings? What does it mean to remove those elements?</p>
<p>The <code>id</code> element has two functions:</p>
<ol>
<li>Documentation</li>
<li>Allow Maven to know when you want to create a <em>new</em> execution and when you want to modify an <em>existing</em> one.</li>
</ol>
<p>The first case is simple: It just allows you to give the execution a meaningful name.</p>
<p>The second case means that Maven comes with default executions which you can see when you run <code>mvn help:effective-pom</code>, for example. If you want to replace/extend an existing execution, you need to use the same <code>id</code>. Maven will then merge the two.</p>
<p>See <a href="http://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-configuring-plugins.html#Using_the_executions_Tag" rel="nofollow">http://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-configuring-plugins.html#Using_the_executions_Tag</a></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Executions of the same id from different POMs are merged.</p>
</blockquote>